that information,

25:22.321 --> 25:25.124 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and then how do they turn that
into a projected
winner?

25:25.157 --> 25:28.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DOMENICO MONTANARO: And us at
NPR, too, we
should say, are relying on the
Associated

25:28.394 --> 25:29.461 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Press' calls.

25:29.495 --> 25:31.163 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What they do is they take three
different
things.

25:31.196 --> 25:34.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They take historical data, they
take the exit
polls, and they take actual
results.

25:34.166 --> 25:39.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they will do with exit
polling information
is, they will go into places
that are barometer

25:39.037 --> 25:40.939 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
precincts, for example.

25:40.973 --> 25:45.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when they get some actual
information
or they get exit poll
information that shows

25:45.144 --> 25:47.646 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
