and the exit
polls back it up.

26:00.559 --> 26:04.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In other words, a
state that's
been reliably Republican or
reliably Democratic.

26:04.363 --> 26:06.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DOMENICO MONTANARO: Yes, like a
New York or
California or something.

26:06.598 --> 26:10.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And those are the
states that
we expect to be called as soon
as the polls

26:10.335 --> 26:12.104 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
close, or very shortly after.

26:12.137 --> 26:13.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DOMENICO MONTANARO: That's
right.

26:14.006 --> 26:16.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's the ones
