Michigan, where he's unlikely to
win.

34:54.826 --> 34:56.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Andra, I want to
ask you about
Georgia.

34:56.494 --> 34:57.829 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's a state you know very well.

34:57.862 --> 35:00.065 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You're teaching there right now
at Emory.

35:00.098 --> 35:04.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is not a state that Hillary
Clinton spent
time in, but the Democrats sure
are pulling

35:04.602 --> 35:08.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
out all the stops trying to get
out the vote
that they think could go to her.

35:08.673 --> 35:10.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What does that look like right
now?

35:10.475 --> 35:12.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDRA GILLESPIE: Well, right
now, most of
the polls suggest that Donald
Trump will still

35:12.377 --> 35:17.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
win the state, but the margin is
probably
going to be even more narrow
than it was 2008.

35:17.382 --> 35:20.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So that's something that's
really, really
important to think about.

35:20.385 --> 35:24.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Democratic Party of Georgia
has spent
months trying to convince the
DNC that this

35:24.122 --> 35:26.124 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was a state that was worth
investing in.

35:26.157 --> 35:27.792 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And this actually shows that.

35:27.826 --> 35:30.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In particular in Georgia, I'm
going to be
paying attention to Gwinnett
County.

35:30.562 --> 35:32.330 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is a Republican stronghold.

35:32.364 --> 35:38.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, demographically, it has
shifted so a
majority of the voters are now
voters of color.

35:38.136 --> 35:42.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If they vote Democratic, then
that represents
the change that the Democratic
Party in Georgia

35:42.407 --> 35:44.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has been predicting for the last
five years
in the state.

35:44.743 --> 35:48.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And isn't it also
challenging
too because it also has a high
concentration

35:48.780 --> 35:49.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of white college-educated
voters.

35:50.015 --> 35:50.949 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ANDRA GILLESPIE: White
college-educated voters.

35:50.982 --> 35:52.784 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY WALTER: So, you get both of
those.

35:52.817 --> 35:55.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDRA GILLESPIE: At the same
time, in addition
to sort of looking west in
Fulton and Cobb

35:55.387 --> 35:56.354 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
County as well.

35:56.388 --> 35:58.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: Agreed.

35:58.223 --> 35:59.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Which reminds us
that education
is something else we're going to
be watching

36:00.025 --> 36:02.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out for tomorrow night, those
voters with
and without a college education
and how they

36:02.494 --> 36:03.461 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
divide.

36:03.495 --> 36:04.729 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Yes.

36:04.763 --> 36:06.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right, it's
great to have
all of you.

36:06.798 --> 36:08.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Amy Walter, Andra Gillespie,
Susan Page, thank
you.

36:08.299 --> 36:09.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SUSAN PAGE: Thank you.

36:09.300 --> 36:10.268 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANDRA GILLESPIE: Thank you.

