hearts.

46:37.161 --> 46:39.030 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here is a sample of their
responses.

46:39.063 --> 46:42.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The project is called Letters to
the Next
President.

46:42.266 --> 46:46.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CYNCERE PRESTON, Student: Both
candidates
should consider affordable
tuition plans,

46:46.971 --> 46:50.141 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
because no one should be
deprived their right
to further their education.

46:50.174 --> 46:54.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My mother works a second job
just to help
pay for my college fees, so I'm
working extra

46:54.412 --> 46:57.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hard in school, so I can receive
as many scholarships
as possible.

46:57.682 --> 47:00.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DULCE SANABRIA, Student: I would
like our
next president to talk about
environmental

47:00.151 --> 47:04.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
issues in a way that actually
makes us feel
inclined to do something about
them.

47:04.388 --> 47:07.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's difficult to put ourselves
in a place
where we actually understand the
negative

47:07.825 --> 47:11.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
impact that we're creating with
the pollution
that we make with things that we
think are

47:11.295 --> 47:14.965 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
necessities like cars or
factories, when,
in reality, those things are not
going to

47:14.999 --> 47:17.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
matter at all if we don't have a
healthy enough
planet to live on.

47:17.301 --> 47:20.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAZLYN MIRANDA-MORALES, Student:
I want the
next president to focus on the
immigration

47:20.938 --> 47:22.673 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
crisis.

47:22.707 --> 47:26.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people are living with fear
of being
deported and having their
families destroyed.

47:26.377 --> 47:30.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The next president should find a
path toward
citizenship for immigrants who
have been longtime

47:30.848 --> 47:32.750 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
residents of our country.

47:32.783 --> 47:37.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead of being treated like
criminals, they
should be rewarded for the
positive contributions

47:37.855 --> 47:40.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they are making in our economy
and society.

47:40.057 --> 47:43.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW RUIZ, Student: What I
want to tell
the next president is that we
need to bring

47:43.828 --> 47:45.596 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
God back into our government.

47:45.629 --> 47:49.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The term separation of church
and state means
that, -- and according to
letters written

47:49.900 --> 47:54.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by Thomas Jefferson -- that the
government
shall not interfere with church
teachings.

47:54.171 --> 47:57.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is important, because we
have taken it
out of context saying that the
church has

47:57.975 --> 47:59.910 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
no right to be in the
government.

47:59.944 --> 48:03.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When God was in our government,
our country
was truly good.

48:03.280 --> 48:05.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
No Democrat or Republican can
fix it.

48:05.483 --> 48:07.351 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Only God can.

48:07.384 --> 48:09.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ABBY ROSS, Student: And I want
the next president
to know that women deserve equal
pay to men.

48:09.820 --> 48:12.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is America, and we are
known for our
freedom.

48:12.289 --> 48:16.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Women are earning more college
and graduate
degrees than men, but are still
earning 79

48:16.460 --> 48:17.962 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cents to the dollar.

48:17.995 --> 48:20.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is our time to be paid
equally, and it
was our time a long time ago.

48:20.898 --> 48:25.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GENEVA VANHORN, Student: I
believe that homelessness
is something that we need to
address in the

48:25.169 --> 48:26.804 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
upcoming election.

48:26.837 --> 48:31.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I believe that we need to help
people who
have lower privileges get up off
of their

48:31.876 --> 48:36.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
feet, because it's not always
their fault
why they made it their in the
first place.

48:36.447 --> 48:40.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It could have been something
like a spike
in taxes that caused them to
lose their home

48:41.018 --> 48:42.820 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and end up on the streets, like
I did.

48:42.853 --> 48:47.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While I was on the streets, I
realized basic
necessities like food and water
were almost

48:47.892 --> 48:52.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
impossible to come by, and
people treated
you as if you were a lesser
human being.

48:52.196 --> 48:54.165 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we need to come together.

48:54.198 --> 48:58.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And whatever excess we have, we
have to use
to bring those people up off
their feet, so

48:58.502 --> 49:00.504 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they can be a useful member of
our communities.

49:00.538 --> 49:04.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TAYLOR KIKU ISHIMOTO, Student: I
would like
to tell the next president that
there are

49:04.074 --> 49:07.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
415,000 children all over
America in foster
care systems.

49:07.845 --> 49:11.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When they exit the foster care
system, 50
percent of them will be
unemployed, 50 percent

49:11.916 --> 49:15.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of them will be homeless, and 33
percent will
have to go on public assistance.

49:15.186 --> 49:20.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL INTRIERI, Student: I
want the next
president to help protect
children like me

49:20.991 --> 49:24.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from violence that has been
going around our
nation.

49:24.461 --> 49:35.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Going to school every day is
hard for us thinking
that we are unsafe and our lives
can be threatened

49:35.739 --> 49:37.608 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at any moment.

49:37.641 --> 49:40.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANTE FAISON, Student: So, Mrs.
Chief Executive
or Mr. Head of State, if you
want to get these

49:40.344 --> 49:42.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
votes, then you have got to be
the one to
make this change.

49:42.947 --> 49:47.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Give us peace of mind and
equality if you
are going to step onto this
grander stage,

49:47.218 --> 49:51.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because I'm tired of being
scared to walk
the streets as blood and bullets
rain.

49:51.222 --> 49:55.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's to stop another brother
from taking
a gunshot to the head or through
his chest?

49:55.893 --> 49:59.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dear America, I'm another
statistic, depending
on which way you see me.

49:59.964 --> 50:02.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You built him a statue, but your
law enforcement
soils what he was dreaming.

50:02.800 --> 50:05.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a whole monument to him
because he
signed off on our freedom.

50:05.402 --> 50:08.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
